<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,151,680]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
For the diagnosis of this species see 
<bibRefCitation author="Hendrich, L. &amp; Mazzoldi, P." box="[639,988,461,487]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref63602" refString="Hendrich, L. &amp; Mazzoldi, P. (1995) Nebrioporus sichuanensis n. sp. - ein neuer Schwimmkafer aus Nordsichuan, China (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae). Entomologische Zeitschrift, 105 (1 / 2), 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="1995">Hendrich &amp; Mazzoldi (1995)</bibRefCitation>
and Toledo (1988). The discovery of some specimens from continental 
<collectingCountry box="[558,628,500,526]" name="China" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">China</collectingCountry>
confirmed the presence of the species in this territory. Although 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1884" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Nebrioporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hostilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">N. hostilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is often difficult to recognise from 
<taxonomicName box="[668,809,538,563]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Deronectes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="airumlus">
<emphasis box="[668,809,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">N. airumlus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Guignot" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[870,1002,538,563]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Nebrioporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brownei">
<emphasis box="[870,1002,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">N. brownei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the shape and length of male inner claws and the parameres allows the recognition of males of these species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
